cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a concatenated coding scheme and discusses the optimization of the degree distribution of the inner code ensemble to minimize data-flow. This is a key topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the design of a low-complexity FEC scheme, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the tradeoff between required signal-to-noise ratio and decoding complexity, which is a topic in systems and control. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the complexity reduction achieved by leaving some inner codeword bits completely uncoded, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity reduction achieved by optimizing the degree distribution of the inner-code ensemble, which is a topic in computational complexity.
